{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/remove-powered-by-shopify-from-footer","result":{"pageContext":{"id":78,"date":"2020-11-01T18:38:47","date_gmt":"2020-11-01T18:38:47","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=78"},"modified":"2021-01-01T02:25:27","modified_gmt":"2021-01-01T02:25:27","slug":"remove-powered-by-shopify-from-footer","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/remove-powered-by-shopify-from-footer/","title":{"rendered":"Remove &#8220;Powered by Shopify&#8221; from footer"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Traditionally themes made and distributed by Shopify come with a copyright message at the very bottom, located in the footer, that says &#8220;<em>powered by Shopify</em>&#8220;.<br><br>Usually this option is hard-coded in and does not offer an option to turn it on/off at your customize page. In this post I&#8217;ll be showing you how you can locate and remove it.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Locating the code</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The instructions below were tested with the <strong>Debut</strong> theme but just for the sake of example. You should be able to achieve this in any Shopify theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>In your Shopify admin, go to <strong>Online Store</strong> &gt; <strong>Themes </strong>&gt; <strong>Actions </strong>&gt; <strong>Edit Code;</strong></li><li>Find the file named <strong>footer.liquid</strong></li><li>Press CTRL +F (or CMD + F on Mac) and search for the following code:<br><strong><code>powered_by</code></strong></li><li>You&#8217;ll likely end up finding multiple instances of this code. Delete the entire line of every single one that you find.</li></ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Before<strong>:</strong><br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"771\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1200x771.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-80\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1200x771.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-600x386.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-768x494.png 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image.png 1268w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>After:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"832\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1-1200x832.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-81\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1-1200x832.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1-600x416.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1-768x532.png 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/image-1.png 1267w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn how to remove the Shopify copyright text from your theme&#8217;s footer.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":83,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[154],"image_alt":"Website with a red arrow pointing at the footer's text. The text says \"Powered By Shopify\".","acf":[],"featured_image_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/powered-by-600x311.jpg","featured_image_small_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/powered-by-100x100.jpg","featured_image_large_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/powered-by-1200x622.jpg","post_count":null,"categories_names":["Blog"],"tag_names":["Code Tutorial"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/78"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"